        "title": "feat(vector): add turbovec search backend",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a reusable vector search backend surface to `crawlkit/vector`.\n\n- keeps exact cosine search as the default backend\n- adds an optional Python `turbovec` bridge backend\n- validates the turbovec dimension contract: dimensions must be divisible by 8\n- adds hermetic bridge tests plus an opt-in real-wheel integration test\n\n## Release order\n\nMerge this first, then tag the next crawlkit patch release. Downstream app branches should move from the pseudo-version to the released crawlkit tag before app releases.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `GOWORK=off go mod tidy`\n- `git diff --exit-code -- go.mod go.sum`\n- `GOWORK=off go vet ./...`\n- `GOWORK=off go test -count=1 ./...`\n- `CRAWLKIT_TURBOVEC_INTEGRATION=1 GOWORK=off go test -count=1 ./vector -run TestSearchTurboVecRealPython -v` with a temp install of `turbovec==0.7.0` and `numpy`\n",
